HEADWORD: Gowan
<hw>Gow"an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Scot., fr. Gael.
<ets>gugan</ets> bud, flower, daisy.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The daisy,
or mountain daisy.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And pu'd the <qex>gowans</qex> fine.</q>
<rj><qau>Burns.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Decomposed granite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gowany</ent>⟦br⟧
